WEBVTT

00:00.083 --> 00:01.585
[Katie barking]

00:02.836 --> 00:04.588
[grunting]

00:04.588 --> 00:06.507
- [dramatic music playing]
- [barking]

00:06.507 --> 00:09.176
[grunting]

00:09.176 --> 00:11.678
Get off!
[shouting]

00:17.809 --> 00:20.103
Get off! Get off!

00:22.231 --> 00:23.607
Get off!
[whimpers, barks]

00:23.607 --> 00:26.401
♪

00:28.278 --> 00:29.238
[grunts]

00:30.113 --> 00:32.115
[growling]

00:35.994 --> 00:37.996
[barking in distance]
[panting]

00:53.679 --> 00:55.681
[engine approaches]

00:58.433 --> 01:00.435
[car door opens, closes]

01:02.020 --> 01:04.940
[door creaks, closes]

01:05.941 --> 01:07.651
[metal clatters in distance]

01:09.570 --> 01:12.281
TYLER:
You know,

01:12.281 --> 01:16.994
there's a special place in hell
for people who hurt dogs.

01:17.995 --> 01:20.581
[chuckles]
You're lucky she's okay,

01:20.581 --> 01:22.583
because if you had hurt her,
I would...

01:22.583 --> 01:25.544
[dark music plays]

01:25.544 --> 01:27.379
♪

01:27.379 --> 01:29.882
I would really, really
have to take my time

01:29.882 --> 01:31.884
killing you, Victor.

01:31.884 --> 01:34.469
That girl, she's, um...

01:38.098 --> 01:40.225
...she's my heart and soul.

01:40.225 --> 01:42.936
In fact...

01:42.936 --> 01:45.647
the first time
that I won a bid to hunt,

01:45.647 --> 01:51.028
they wouldn't approve Katie
as my in-game weapon.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.534
[shouting]

02:00.621 --> 02:02.831
So I had to give a presentation.

02:02.831 --> 02:07.085
The history of man and dog
hunting together...

02:09.755 --> 02:11.757
[metal clatters]

02:15.344 --> 02:19.139
...from its infancy
20,000 years ago

02:19.139 --> 02:21.517
to the great fox hunts
of England

02:21.517 --> 02:25.812
to bloodhounds and good old boys
hunting in the Bayou today.

02:25.812 --> 02:29.942
[exhales] All to convince
Miles that Katie

02:29.942 --> 02:32.486
didn't violate
the spirit of the game.

02:32.486 --> 02:34.488
[snorts]

02:34.488 --> 02:36.406
Now, I don't know
if it was my speech

02:36.406 --> 02:38.534
or if it was my checkbook,

02:38.534 --> 02:43.914
but here I am, with Katie,
on our third hunt together.

02:47.459 --> 02:49.878
It doesn't have to take all day.

02:49.878 --> 02:52.214
You know Katie's gonna find you.

02:52.214 --> 02:54.258
[clattering]

02:56.260 --> 02:57.469
There you are.

03:00.973 --> 03:02.558
[Katie barking]

03:04.560 --> 03:07.604
My girl will be here soon,
and then we'll get to it.

03:07.604 --> 03:10.858
[chuckles]
I saw you downtown.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.694
You'd been steadily
heading south.

03:13.694 --> 03:16.947
You should've mixed it up
a little. Right?

03:16.947 --> 03:19.157
Then I saw you hail a cab,
so I got into my car

03:19.157 --> 03:20.993
and then I just

03:20.993 --> 03:24.079
followed you straight here
to scenic Staten Island.

03:24.079 --> 03:25.539
You know, that SUV you got

03:25.539 --> 03:27.416
is a little low-rent
to be a billionaire.

03:27.416 --> 03:30.252
You a... you a proxy?

03:30.252 --> 03:32.337
No.

03:32.337 --> 03:35.048
I have more money
than Wells Fargo.

03:35.048 --> 03:36.633
[laughs]

03:36.633 --> 03:39.970
I-I-I inherited.

03:39.970 --> 03:41.638
Inherited it, but, uh, my family

03:41.638 --> 03:44.808
made their fortune
in heavy construction.

03:45.851 --> 03:48.395
Uh-uh-uh.

03:48.395 --> 03:51.356
These hunting trophies of mine,
they're probably the only things

03:51.356 --> 03:55.611
that I've ever earned
in my life. You know?

03:55.611 --> 03:57.988
It's probably why I do it.

03:57.988 --> 04:02.826
While, uh, my Katie's trying
to find a way up here,

04:02.826 --> 04:05.704
you just remember that, uh,

04:05.704 --> 04:09.374
she always loves it
when I tenderize her meat first.

04:09.374 --> 04:11.210
You don't got to do this.

04:11.210 --> 04:12.544
Come here.

04:12.544 --> 04:14.254
[yells]

04:14.254 --> 04:16.256
[screams]

04:16.256 --> 04:18.008
[coughs]

04:18.008 --> 04:20.093
[wheezing]

04:22.679 --> 04:24.640
[grunts]

04:24.640 --> 04:27.226
You son of a bitch!

04:28.268 --> 04:30.020
[screaming]

04:31.438 --> 04:34.650
[suspenseful music plays]

04:34.650 --> 04:35.776
♪

04:35.776 --> 04:37.361
[Katie barking in distance]

04:41.615 --> 04:42.824
[truck door closes]

04:42.824 --> 04:44.576
[engine starts]
[music playing]

04:44.576 --> 04:45.619
Hey!

04:45.619 --> 04:47.120
♪ I don't want you back ♪

04:47.120 --> 04:48.121
♪ You can't handle that ♪

04:48.121 --> 04:50.916
♪ Wonderbread... ♪

04:50.916 --> 04:52.209
[barking]

04:57.506 --> 04:59.258
Katie!

05:00.467 --> 05:01.885
Come.

05:12.855 --> 05:15.190
[tires screech]

05:15.190 --> 05:17.276
Oh, fuck me!

05:17.276 --> 05:20.279
[suspenseful music plays]

05:20.279 --> 05:23.448
♪

05:30.038 --> 05:31.707
[laughs]

05:43.677 --> 05:45.095
Oh!
[tires screeching]

05:49.641 --> 05:50.851
[engine revs]

05:54.813 --> 05:56.023
[growling, barking]

06:00.652 --> 06:01.820
Kill, Katie girl.

06:01.820 --> 06:03.697
[barking]

06:03.697 --> 06:06.825
[laughs]

06:06.825 --> 06:09.870
[dramatic music plays]

06:09.870 --> 06:11.622
♪

06:15.751 --> 06:18.086
MAN: Hey! Get the hell
out of my boat!

06:18.086 --> 06:19.379
What the fuck?

06:19.379 --> 06:21.632
Oh, shit.

06:21.632 --> 06:23.675
Shit.

06:36.063 --> 06:37.898
Fuck.

06:39.691 --> 06:40.901
Fuck.

06:40.901 --> 06:43.362
[engine revs]

06:44.488 --> 06:45.489
Katie!

06:45.489 --> 06:46.865
- [whimpering]
- Swim to Daddy!

06:48.784 --> 06:50.410
Go get help!

06:51.787 --> 06:53.205
Fuck you, Katie.

06:53.205 --> 06:54.915
- [Katie whimpering]
- [moans]

07:01.797 --> 07:03.340
Katie!

07:05.342 --> 07:08.178
Fuck. Katie!

07:11.890 --> 07:13.517
[gasping]

07:18.188 --> 07:19.523
[helicopter whirring
in distance]

07:19.523 --> 07:21.608
[footsteps approaching]

07:21.608 --> 07:23.861
[indistinct chatter]

07:29.408 --> 07:32.327
Can I speak to you, please?

07:32.327 --> 07:34.037
You can, but may you?

07:34.037 --> 07:36.832
May I speak with you?

07:36.832 --> 07:38.458
- Please?
- How much longer?

07:38.458 --> 07:40.794
Uh, if he continues
on his current trajectory,

07:40.794 --> 07:43.422
he'll be on dry land
in Brooklyn any minute.

07:43.422 --> 07:45.340
[phone chimes]
Connell texted.

07:45.340 --> 07:46.550
He's already at the projected
landing point.

07:46.550 --> 07:49.011
Ah. Well, very good.

07:59.354 --> 08:01.690
Who do you think you are,
storming in here like this?

08:01.690 --> 08:03.192
Look, I have friends in Tech.

08:03.192 --> 08:04.985
I know about the cops and Suero.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.361
I also know
that the Board is pissed.

08:06.361 --> 08:08.197
That's why they sent
for you earlier.

08:08.197 --> 08:10.324
Well, you seem to think
you know a lot of things.

08:10.324 --> 08:12.201
I know I didn't select Suero.

08:12.201 --> 08:13.952
So if the board's gonna
come down on anyone,

08:13.952 --> 08:15.287
I don't want it to be me.

08:15.287 --> 08:16.914
What do you think
I told them?

08:18.457 --> 08:21.502
Look, months ago,
when Suero was selected, by me,

08:21.502 --> 08:23.879
I admittedly took
all the credit.

08:23.879 --> 08:26.798
So when things go sideways,
as they sometimes do,

08:26.798 --> 08:28.550
I will get all the blame.

08:28.550 --> 08:30.594
The pitfall of being boss.

08:30.594 --> 08:33.347
You are in absolutely
no jeopardy.

08:34.806 --> 08:38.185
What's the keystone of
the mentor/protege relationship?

08:38.185 --> 08:41.146
Loyalty.

08:41.146 --> 08:44.650
Now, since I found you hustling
in that Tampa pool hall,

08:44.650 --> 08:45.859
haven't I protected you?

08:45.859 --> 08:47.945
[somber music plays]

08:47.945 --> 08:50.447
However, it is
a serious breach of propriety

08:50.447 --> 08:53.116
to barge into my control room
without invitation.

08:55.702 --> 08:57.329
Let's not let that happen again.

08:57.329 --> 08:59.081
Yes, sir.

08:59.081 --> 09:02.125
♪

09:22.688 --> 09:24.356
[siren whoops]

09:26.942 --> 09:28.360
Shit.

09:33.156 --> 09:34.950
How you boys doing?
MANNING: Good.

09:34.950 --> 09:36.451
How about yourself?

09:36.451 --> 09:37.953
Eh, can't complain.

09:37.953 --> 09:40.038
MANNING: Listen.
We got a report of a boat

09:40.038 --> 09:42.040
matching this description,
heading in this direction,

09:42.040 --> 09:45.210
stolen from Staten Island,
so what's going on?

09:46.920 --> 09:48.672
Seriously?

09:48.672 --> 09:52.050
This is my boat.
My parents left this boat to me.

09:52.050 --> 09:54.636
Inherited a boat, huh?
Times are tough.

09:54.636 --> 09:56.305
Yeah, well, my asshole brother
swears it's his.

09:56.305 --> 09:58.015
But I got all the paperwork.

10:02.811 --> 10:05.314
Look, I don't want
a problem, all right?

10:05.314 --> 10:08.108
So how about,
as a sign of good faith,

10:08.108 --> 10:10.986
I'll give you guys the keys so
you know I'm not gonna run off,

10:10.986 --> 10:12.237
and tomorrow, I'll bring
the ownership documents

10:12.237 --> 10:13.488
to the precinct.

10:16.283 --> 10:17.868
Think it's best
you come with us.

10:19.536 --> 10:21.288
No problem.

10:21.288 --> 10:22.623
[suspenseful music plays]

10:22.623 --> 10:24.583
Sh-- No, no!

10:25.626 --> 10:26.793
[grunts]

10:26.793 --> 10:28.504
MANNING: You have
the right to remain silent.

10:28.504 --> 10:31.131
Anything you say can
and will be held against you

10:31.131 --> 10:33.050
in a court of law.

10:35.802 --> 10:38.722
[dark music plays]

10:38.722 --> 10:40.724
♪

10:40.724 --> 10:42.726
There's been a development.

10:42.726 --> 10:44.686
It appears Victor Suero
just became

10:44.686 --> 10:47.439
a permanent player in the game.
